message.content:
Below is one reasonable way to “read off” the little house in the picture and match it to the dictionary blocks without rotating or reorienting any of them:

1)  Structure Description  
• Layers and Count.  
  – Bottom Layer: 4 cubes forming a 2 × 2 “footprint.”  
     • 2 red cubes (front‐left, back‐left)  
     • 2 orange cubes (front‐right, back‐right)  
  – Second Layer (“Green Belt”): 4 horizontally oriented green rectangular blocks, one on each side atop the bottom cubes, forming a ring.  
  – Top Layer (Roof): 1 orange wedge block centered on top.  
• Overall Shape.  
  – Viewed from the front, the lower layer is red on the left and orange on the right.  
  – A continuous green band (four separate green pieces) sits above the cubes.  
  – A single orange “roof” wedge caps the structure.

2)  Matching Dictionary Blocks  
• Red cubes: use block 4 (twice)  
• Orange cubes: use block 3 (twice)  
• Green rectangular blocks (horizontal): use block 6 (four times)  
• Orange wedge (front‐to‐back slope): use block 14 (once)

3)  Assembly Order  
Use the following sequence (one move per block) to build from bottom to top:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 4  
  Step2: Move block with index 4  
  Step3: Move block with index 3  
  Step4: Move block with index 3  
  Step5: Move block with index 6  
  Step6: Move block with index 6  
  Step7: Move block with index 6  
  Step8: Move block with index 6  
  Step9: Move block with index 14  
}
